/**
 * /ontology/identity — Identity & classification.
 *
 * The authored conceptual layer: the implicit-Property crux (ODR-0005 — the
 * three-class Property/LegalEstate/RegisteredTitle split, UPRN as a contingent
 * Quality, the named hard cases) and the classification doctrine (ODR-0027 —
 * facets / coded SKOS over subclass trees; Roles never subclass a Kind;
 * evidence as RoleMixin + evidenceType facet).
 *
 * No build-time corpus counts are needed here; the page is prose harvested
 * from ODR-0005 and ODR-0027. Same Layout/PageMeta shape as the section.
 */
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '@/components/PageMeta.astro';

// ODR-0005 §3a — the five named hard cases the opda:Property IC is exercised over.
const HARD_CASES = [
  ['Demolition', 'The physical thing ceases; the LegalEstate and RegisteredTitle may persist (a cleared plot is still an estate).'],
  ['Subdivision', 'One Property becomes many — new UPRNs issue; identity does not survive a split into distinct material continua.'],
  ['Merger', 'Many Properties become one; identity of the constituents ends.'],
  ['Replacement (rebuild on the same plot)', 'A new Property iff the legal record asserts discontinuity (title closure + re-registration, or a new UPRN with no prov:wasDerivedFrom chain). Routine knock-down-rebuild without registry discontinuity PRESERVES identity — matching conveyancer practice. Listed-building heritage exception via a SHACL profile.'],
  ['Boundary modification', 'A boundary change without registry discontinuity preserves identity; a transfer of land that re-registers does not.'],
];

// ODR-0027 — the classification doctrine rules (R1, R2, R3, R4, R5, R6).
const DOCTRINE = [
  ['R1 — isMemberOf is the default; isA is the exception',
   'Classification (what type a thing is) is done by coded set-membership — isMemberOf a skos:ConceptScheme — by default. Mint an OWL subclass (isA / rdfs:subClassOf) ONLY for a genuine Kind that carries its own identity criterion (and/or a distinct relational structure SHACL must enforce per-type). One class, a value that varies, is the rule; a subclass per coded value is the anti-pattern.'],
  ['R2 — a facet is NOT a classification',
   'A facet is the set of type-specific attributes an entity of a given type bears — it presupposes the type and says nothing about what the type is. opda:attestedBy and opda:documentReference are facets. opda:evidenceType is NOT a facet — it is an isMemberOf classifier (it states the kind). (opda overloads "facet" to mean type-borne attributes, not an ISO-25964 classification axis.)'],
  ['R3 — Roles are anti-rigid → NEVER rdfs:subClassOf a Kind',
   'A Role is borne via a roleOf / playedBy relation (founded by the relevant Relator/Activity), with a coded isMemberOf classifier where the role sub-divides — never rdfs:subClassOf the bearer Kind. opda already does this for opda:Seller / opda:Buyer (RoleMixin) and opda:Proprietor (Role); the doctrine generalises it.'],
  ['R4 — every enumeration is a SKOS scheme',
   'Every closed value-space, status set, kind-discriminator, and UFO-stereotype axis is a skos:ConceptScheme of skos:Concepts, referenced by a coded value — never an owl:oneOf bag and never an rdfs:subClassOf enumeration. A scheme member binds to an OWL Kind by skos:exactMatch only where that Kind independently earns isA — never owl:sameAs.'],
  ['R5 — enforcement is value-keyed, not class-keyed',
   'rdfs:domain / rdfs:range are informative, never evaluated. SHACL is the enforcement layer, and per-type obligations are value-keyed on the isMemberOf classifier (sh:targetSubjectsOf + a value-guarded material implication in SHACL-Core), not keyed on a subclass sh:targetClass (which is entailment-relative and silently passes a value-recorded instance). Class-targeting is correct in exactly one place: a type↔value coherence shape.'],
  ['R6 — evidence is a Role, not a Kind tree',
   'opda:Evidence is the role target (a RoleMixin); evidence-kind is an isMemberOf coded classification (opda:evidenceType → opda:EvidenceMethodScheme), not a subclass tree. The three …Evidence rdfs:subClassOf opda:Evidence axioms are retired; kind-specific attributes become facets borne by the role. (This reverses session-036\'s keep-the-subclasses disposition; its value-keyed-enforcement finding stands.)'],
];
